      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ")",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It appears, therefore, that the original reading of the Heb. text was, “And this house shall become ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ruinous heaps”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "‘îyîn,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " “heaps,” not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "‘elyôn,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " “high”). (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Micah 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The mistake is as old as the LXX., ",
        "children": []
